<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``If America has prevailed because it is a superpower in the air
and the sea, it will inevitably be defeated in Libya. We, as well as
the fish, are awaiting them.'' _ Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi on
the skirmish Wednesday over the Mediterranean in which U.S. Navy jet
fighters shot down two Libyan MiG-23 planes.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``This is not some emotional commitment to help `the poor little
birdies,' It's more a matter of we made the mess and let's clean it
up and develop a technology for heading this off.'' _ Alice Berkner,
a Vancouver, Wash., bird expert, who heads the ``Dirty Bird
Hospital'' in Ocean Shores, Wash., where thousands of sea birds were
taken for cleaning following one of the Pacific Northwest's worst
oil spills.
