according to Velez Buie, activities director at the home.
   ``When they were 103, somebody asked Maggie who was the last
president they voted for and she said she didn't know but it was a
Republican,'' Ms. Buie said. She said both women need wheelchairs to
get around and that neither could talk on the phone.
   Helms wrote the letter that Bush and the senators autographed.
``Without question, you are the oldest twins who are members of any
political party,'' he wrote.
   The Guinness Book of World Records recognizes the sisters as the
world's oldest living twins.
