<FIRST>r a PM-SamaritanKilled     01-05 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Samaritan Killed,0238</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Stops to Offer Aid; Dies In Freak Accident</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DENNIS GEORGATOS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who stopped to help a driver with a flat
tire was struck and killed by a tire that broke loose from a passing
truck, authorities said.
   Kevin Scott Stratford, a 23-year-old ranch hand from Carlsbad,
died early Wednesday at a ramp on Interstate 5 in Cardiff, where he
had pulled his car behind the disabled vehicle, said California
Highway Patrol spokesman Jerry Bohrer.
   ``The odds of something like this happening are astronomical,''
Bohrer said. ``It's hard to conceive.''
   The driver of the disabled car had told Stratford he didn't have
the tools to change the tire, Bohrer said.
   ``Stratford goes back to the trunk of his car and retrieves a
toolbox when along comes a southbound truck,'' he said. ``It loses
two tires off the rear axle, one of which hits Stratford as he turns
around from the trunk ... and killed him instantly.''
   The other tire went across the freeway, causing a minor three-car
collision. The driver of the tanker truck pulled safely off the
road, Bohrer said.
   Bohrer said it was not clear why the tires broke loose. ``Our
motor carrier people are doing a detailed inspection to establish
the reason, but it's going to be a few days before (their
investigation) is finalized,'' he said.
</TEXT>
