<DATELINE>STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Sen. John Stennis has gone back
to college.
   The 87-year-old Democrat, who retired this week after 41 years in
Washington, has become ``executive in residence'' at his alma mater,
Mississippi State University.
   Stennis, who graduated in 1923, will maintain his home in DeKalb,
about 50 miles south of the campus, but he said he'll spend most of
his time at Mississippi State.
   He plans to consult with students and faculty, hold seminars for
students, serve as a guest lecturer and assist librarians in
organizing his official papers.
   ``I feel like I'm really coming home,'' Stennis said Wednesday.
``I came here as an 18-year-old boy, and I never stopped being
grateful for the good start I got here.''
