<FIRST>u f BC-AutoProdn     01-05 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Auto Production Resumes after Holiday Break</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
171,936 cars and light trucks this week after resuming work
following Christmas vacation, Ward's Automotive Reports said
Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 182,374 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 109,566 cars this week,
compared with 105,338 in the same week in 1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 62,370,
compared with last year's 77,036.
   Canadian automakers were to build 13,061 cars this week, down
from last year's 22,486.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 16,872, compared
with 16,372 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
