<FIRST>r f AM-Dun&amp;Bradstreet     01-05 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Dun &amp; Bradstreet,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dun &amp; Bradstreet Acquires Sales Technologies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dun &amp; Bradstreet Corp. said Thursday it has
acquired Sales Technologies Inc., an Atlanta-based supplier of
automation systems used by the sales force.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
   Dun &amp; Bradstreet, a marketer of business information and related
services, said its new acquisition will operate as an independent
unit.
   Sales Technologies' systems are based on lap-top computer
technology and can be used in a range of functions, including
account planning, call reporting and electronic mail, Dun &amp;
Bradstreet said.
   Its customers include manufacturers of pharmaceutical and medical
supplies, consumer goods and industrial products and chemicals.
   ``ST is the leader in the market it serves and we also expect it
to serve as a vehicle for automating the delivery of _ and expanding
the use of _ data provided by IMS International, Nielsen Marketing
Research and other D&amp;B units,'' said Charles W. Moritz, chairman and
chief executive officer of Dun &amp; Bradstreet.
